{
  "text": "Concerning tamoxifen alone treatment group, tamoxifen reduced depressive-like behavior in the forced swim test. The results are consistent with previous report [CITATION_1] . However, it has been reported that tamoxifen by itself produced no changes in immobility time in the forced swim test [CITATION_2] . Tamoxifen alone tendency to increase pCREB, pCREB/CREB and significantly increased BDNF levels in the hippocampus in the ovariectomized mice. These results may be consistent with our behavior study.",
